<title id="207">[RC] taskbody: TiS Initializing Controller-0</title>
<rcbody>
        <taskbody id="taskbody_N10011_N1000E_N10001">
            <prereq id="prereq_N1002B_N10028_N10001" id="166">
                <p id="169">Before installing the ISO image, ensure the following:</p>
                <ul id="ul_p5w_hwh_g4">
                    <li id="172">
                        <p id="175">The host meets the hardware requirements for a
                            controller.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li id="90">
                        <p id="10">You have terminal-server access to the host, so that you
                            can monitor messages during initialization.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li id="178">
                        <p id="181">The management, OAM, and optional infrastructure
                            networks are planned, set up, and connected.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li id="91">
                        <p id="92">All other hosts on the system are powered off.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li id="93">
                        <p id="94">You have reviewed the Release Notes for any additional
                            information pertaining to installation. </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </prereq>
            <steps id="all_steps">
                <step id="power_on_host" id="61">
                    <cmd id="62">Power on the host to be configured as <nameliteral id="184">controller-0</nameliteral>.</cmd>
                </step>
                <step id="configure_BIOS_for_boot" id="11">
                    <cmd id="12">Configure the host BIOS boot sequence to boot from a USB
                        removable storage device.</cmd>
                </step>
                <step id="insert_USB_flash_drive" id="14">
                    <cmd id="15">Insert the USB flash drive and boot the host.</cmd>
                    <stepresult id="16">
                        <p id="17">The installer welcome screen appears.</p>
                        <fig id="fig_N10059_N10052_N1004B_N1003C_N10028_N10001" id="18">
                            <title id="19">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Installer Welcome Screen</title>
                            <image href="jow1433084986736.image" id="image_yzn_skg_fs" id="208">
                                <alt id="209">TiS Installer screen (basic)</alt>
                            </image>
                            <!-- image href="jow1404333487370.image" id="image_wvh_5kg_fs">
                                <alt>TiS Installer screen with two-server configuration</alt>
                            </image -->
                        </fig>
                    </stepresult>
                </step>
                <step id="select_installation_type" id="21">
                    <cmd id="22">Select the type of installation and the display device to
                        be used during initialization, and then press <userinput id="23">Enter</userinput>.</cmd>
                    <info id="145">
                        <!-- p id="205">To install a standalone controller, select from the
                            first group.</p -->
                        <dl>
                            <dlentry id="187">
                                <dt id="190"><nameliteral id="193">Serial Controller
                                        Node Install</nameliteral> (default)</dt>
                                <dd id="196">
                                    <p id="185">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using the serial port to display messages. You can
                                        monitor the port using the terminal server.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry id="199">
                                <dt id="164"><nameliteral id="170">Graphics
                                        Controller Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd id="201">
                                    <p id="203">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using graphics mode to display messages. This
                                        selection works with most console displays.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry id="167">
                                <dt id="179"><nameliteral id="173">Graphics Text
                                        Controller Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd id="176">
                                    <p id="182">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using text mode to display messages. This is a safe
                                        option for nodes that do not support graphics mode.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                        </dl>
                        <!-- p id="206">To install a minimal two-server configuration, in which
                            the controller and compute functions are implemented on a single host,
                            select from the second group.</p>
                        <dl>
                            <dlentry id="188">
                                <dt id="191"><nameliteral id="194">Serial
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral> (default)</dt>
                                <dd id="197">
                                    <p id="186">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using the serial port to display messages. You can
                                        monitor the port using the terminal server.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry id="200">
                                <dt id="165"><nameliteral id="171">Graphics
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd id="202">
                                    <p id="204">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using graphics mode to display messages. This
                                        selection works with most console displays.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry id="168">
                                <dt id="180"><nameliteral id="174">Graphics Text
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd id="177">
                                    <p id="183">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using text mode to display messages. This is a
                                        safe option for nodes that do not support graphics mode.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                        </dl -->
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="monitor_initialization" id="70">
                    <cmd id="71">Monitor the initialization until it is complete.</cmd>
                    <info id="72">
                        <p id="73">The installer initializes the target hard drive with the
                            HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade image. When initialization is complete, a reboot is
                            initiated on the host. </p>
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="remove_usb_flash_drive" id="189">
                    <cmd importance="high" id="192">Immediately remove the USB flash drive
                        from the host to ensure that the host reboots from the hard drive.</cmd>
                    <info id="195">
                        <note id="note_N100C5_N100C2_N100B8_N1004B_N1002E_N10001" id="67" type="caution">
                            <p id="198">If the USB flash drive is still attached when the
                                host reboots, then unless the boot sequence has been configured to
                                prevent it, the host will boot from the USB flash drive again
                                instead of the hard drive.</p>
                        </note>
                        <p id="47"> After a few minutes, the host reboots from the hard
                            drive and displays the <wintitle id="48">GNU GRUB</wintitle>
                            welcome screen.</p>
                        <fig id="fig_N100DB_N100D0_N100C9_N1003C_N10028_N10001" id="49">
                            <image alt="GNU GRUB screen" href="jow1404333488777.image" id="image_jb1_gfz_cn" id="51" width="4in"/>
                        </fig>
                        <p id="52">After a brief delay, the system boots automatically into
                            the HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade image.</p>
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="log_in" id="53">
                    <cmd id="54">Log into the host as <userinput id="55">wrsroot</userinput>, with password <userinput id="56">wrsroot</userinput>.</cmd>
                    <info id="140">
                        <note id="note_N1016E_N1016A_N10156_N1007D_N1002E_N10001" id="149">
                            <p id="150">Typed responses to password prompts are suppressed
                                and do not appear on the display.</p>
                        </note>
                        <p id="142">The first time you log in as <userinput id="143">wrsroot</userinput>, you are required to change your password.</p>
                        <codeblock id="151"><systemoutput id="152">Changing password for wrsroot.
(current) UNIX Password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p id="153">Enter the current password (<nameliteral id="154">wrsroot</nameliteral>).</p>
                        <codeblock id="155"><systemoutput id="156">New password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p id="157">Enter a new password for the <nameliteral id="161">wrsroot </nameliteral>account.</p>
                        <codeblock id="158"><systemoutput id="159">Retype new password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p id="160">Enter the new password again to confirm it.</p>
                    </info>
                </step>
            </steps>
            <result id="result_N10100_N10028_N10001" id="57">
                <p id="58">The host is now ready for configuration as <nameliteral id="144">controller-0</nameliteral>.</p>
            </result>
        </taskbody>
    </rcbody>
